"text"},{"text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"objects to handle the display.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMultiPolyline":{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"An ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline"},{"text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"polylines. For example, you could use a multipolyline shape to represent both","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"sides of a divided highway (dual carriageway), excluding the median (central","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"reservation): each carriageway would be a distinct ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline"},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}],"title":"MLNMultiPolyline","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmultipolyline","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNMultiPolyline"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/docum